sourcesContent:
export const DUMMY_POSTS = [
    {
      id: '1',
      storycover: Story1,
      category: 'Fantasy',
      title: 'Arabian Nights',
      desc: 'Arabian Nights is a collection of captivating Middle Eastern folk tales, featuring stories of love, adventure, and magic. Framed by the clever Scheherazade, who tells tales to save her life, the collection includes iconic stories like Aladdins Wonderful Lamp and "Ali Baba and the Forty Thieves." These timeless narratives have enchanted readers for centuries, offering a glimpse into the rich cultural heritage of the region and the power of storytelling to transcend time and place',
      authorID: 1
    },
    {
      id: '2',
      storycover: Story2,
      category: 'Fiction',
      title: 'Life of Pi',
      desc: 'Life of Pi is a mesmerizing tale of survival and spirituality. Written by Yann Martel, it follows the journey of Pi Patel, a young Indian boy stranded on a lifeboat in the Pacific Ocean with a Bengal tiger named Richard Parker. As Pi navigates the challenges of the open sea, he grapples with profound questions of faith, identity, and the indomitable human spirit.',
      authorID: 2
    },
    {
      id: '3',
      storycover: Story4,
      category: 'Mystery',
      title: 'Sherlock Holmes',
      desc: 'Sherlock Holmes, created by Sir Arthur Conan Doyle, is the iconic detective known for his brilliant mind and keen powers of deduction. Alongside his loyal friend and companion, Dr. John Watson, Holmes tackles perplexing cases and solves mysteries with unmatched precision. From the foggy streets of Victorian London to the countryside estates of England, Holmes adventures have enthralled readers for generations.',
      authorID: 4
    },
    {
      id: '4',
      storycover: Story3,
      category: 'Romance',
      title: 'Half Girlfriend',
      desc: 'Half Girlfriend, penned by Chetan Bhagat, is a contemporary love story set in India. The novel follows the journey of Madhav Jha, a small-town boy from Bihar, and Riya Somani, a sophisticated girl from Delhi. Their unlikely relationship, marked by cultural differences and personal ambitions, explores themes of friendship, love, and the pursuit of dreams in a rapidly changing society.',
      authorID: 3
    },
  ];
